Transport Minister, Fikile Mbalula says a final decision will be announced before the end of March. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng motorists will soon find out what is happening with e-tolls, according to Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula.
He says there has been a back-and-forth in Treasury about what to do with the much-reviled system. READ: e-Tolls a 'heroic failure': Mamabolo Many motorists have refused to pay for years now. Mbalula says a final decision will be announced before the end of this month. READ: The e-toll story not an easy one, says Mbalula "This year, one of the biggest press conferences is going to be about e-tolls, so look ahead for it as it is coming. We are attending to it," he said. "We've got to do it in concurrence with Treasury and then go back to Cabinet. Once Cabinet gives us a green light on the matter, we'll be able to communicate."